STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
John Graham HEADLEY, Appellant. WD 80994 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Filed: January 29, 2019 Steven B. Willibey, Kansas City for appellant. Garrick F. D. Aplin, Jefferson City for respondent. Before Division Three: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, Lisa White Hardwick and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judges

ORDER

Per Curiam

John Headley appeals his convictions and sentences for first-degree statutory sodomy and incest. He contends the evidence was insufficient to support the convictions. Upon review of the briefs and the record, we find no error and affirm the judgment. We have provided the parties with a Memorandum explaining the reasons for our decision, because a published opinion would serve no jurisprudential purpose.

AFFIRMED. Rule 30.25(b).
